{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SUoGwe8HQrPY2NJXDcESxv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` was missing `configure` permission on the `/app` vhost. The permissions were:\n- configure: `\"\"` (empty) — **blocked queue declaration**\n- write: `.*`\n- read: `.*`\n\nDeclaring a queue requires the configure permission (`.*`) on the vhost.\n\n**Fix:** One command — `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — grants full configure/write/read to `app-user` on `/app`.\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer-5cc6dd9c5-hnvg8` is `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts\n- `app-queue` exists in `/app` vhost as type `classic`, durable, with 44 messages (and growing)\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are up and clustered"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":644,"cache_read_input_tokens":35007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":644},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4217ee65-7564-4908-8803-1b499117991f","uuid":"c984e3b2-22c0-4cf0-b8e9-e55c3efca37f","request_id":"req_011Ccc7Enxt3vtq1W2xjuA9Z"}
